<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><title>$ command line ruby cheat sheets</title><link charset="utf-8" href="/style.css" media="screen" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" /></head><body><div class="main"><div class="header"><h1><a href="/">cheat sheets.</a></h1><code class="header">$ command line ruby cheat sheets</code></div></div><div class="content"><pre>Linking apps in Pow

powder [-h|help] - Display usage information 
powder link - Link the current dir to ~/.pow/&lt;current_directory&gt;
powder link [bacon] - Link the current dir to ~/.pow/bacon
powder remove - Unlink current_dir
powder remove [bacon] - Unlink bacon

Working with Pow

powder app log - tail the log of the current app
powder config - Get Pow's current configuration information
powder list - List all the current apps linked in ~/.pow
powder log - Tails the pow log. Not the application log, but the pow log.
powder open - Opens the pow link in a browser
powder open [bacon] - Opens http://bacon.dev in a browser
powder restart - Restart the current app
powder status - Get Pow's current status information
powder version - Returns the current powder version

Install and uninstall Pow

powder install - Installs pow server
powder uninstall - Uninstalls pow server
powder update - Updates pow server

Enable and Disable Pow

powder up - Enable Pow
powder down - Disable Pow</pre></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="footer">Powered by <a href="http://www.sinatrarb.com/">Sinatra</a>,
